Nigerian singer, songwriter Tiwa Savage recently took to her Insta Stories to share a message for companies which are allegedly owing her millions. "I might have to call out these companies that owe me millions," she says. "If you no get, say you no get... no dey use style yan something else. I know how much revenue my brand has generated your brand, don't even try it," she added. Tiwa concluded: "You better SAN WO OLU. Na we get Lagos ooo. Check the contract". This is coming after her amicable departure from Mavin Records and her subsequent songwriting deal with Sony/ATV Music Publishing.